@node DungeonMaster "Dungeon Master 1-2 & Chaos Strikes Back"

These are currently supported:

    DM1 saved games (dungeon & characters)
    CSB saved games (dungeon & characters)
    DM2 saved games (dungeon & characters)
    DM1 dungeons    (dungeon only)
    CSB dungeons    (dungeon only)
    DM2 dungeons    (dungeon only)

Mods to the DUNGEON.DAT file will only show up in a new game. After the
first save, your modified dungeon will become part of a new DMGAME.DAT
file. Existing DMGAME.DAT files use the DUNGEON.DAT file that existed when
that game was first saved.
  For dungeon files, the "Game" information may not be entirely accurate
as far as version or platform, but this will not cause any problems with
editing.
  Even non-Amiga files are supported (this is the only tool for which this
applies), though they have not been tested.

Character viewing/editing:

Not all items are necessarily known by the editor.
  Not every item that is known will necessarily work correctly in the
game; you may need to experiment to find the correct version of an item.
  Invalid items (shown as "!") will definitely not work.

Dungeon viewing/editing:

Chaos Strikes Back: The full (non-prison) dungeon is considered by the
game to be 11 levels (the 11th level is a single square); this is not a
bug in MCE.
  Dungeon Master 2: There is no "9th level"; this is not a bug in MCE.
  The leftmost (arrow) tool will move your party to any desired square.
  The eight central tools can be used to change squares to the desired
type. They will not change objects, stairs or doors.
  The rightmost (door) tool can be used to change doors. With this tool,
clicking on a door will cycle it through open, closed and broken states.
  The left and right cursor keys can be used to change levels.
@endnode

@node EyeOfTheBeholder "Eye of the Beholder 1 & 2"

Hover over an item slot to see what slot is (eg. "Head", "Neck", etc.)
  It is recommended not to edit the quiver, as it seems to be encoded
